#Hardware Requirements

1) Arduino UNO (or compatible board)

2) 4-digit 7-segment display (e.g., TM1637 or common-cathode display)

3) TM1637 display module (recommended for simplicity)

4) Buzzer (optional)

5) Push button (to flip/reset the timer)

6) Jumper wires


#Concept

Countdown timer (like a sand clock). Automatically flips/restarts when it reaches 0. Optionally, use a button to manually flip it.
Display remaining time on 4-digit 7-segment

#Features

Displays countdown in MM:SS format

Resets after reaching 00:00

Manual reset/flip via button

Buzzer alerts when time is up
